Overview: The {{service_name}} API provides programmatic access to {{resource_description}} within the Acme Corp platform. This service handles approximately {{number}} requests per day and is classified as Tier {{tier}} ({{tier_description}}).

Authentication: All API requests must include a valid Bearer token in the Authorization header. Tokens are issued by the Acme Corp Identity Service (OAuth2 client credentials flow). Token lifetime: {{number}} hours. Scopes: {{scope_list}}.

Base URL: https://api.acmecorp.internal/{{service_slug}}/v{{version}}
Staging: https://api.staging.acmecorp.internal/{{service_slug}}/v{{version}}

Endpoints:

GET /{{resource_slug}}
  Description: List all {{resource_type}} resources
  Query params: page (int), per_page (int, max {{number}}), filter (string), sort_by (enum: created_at|updated_at|name)
  Response: 200 OK with paginated array of {{resource_type}} objects

POST /{{resource_slug}}
  Description: Create a new {{resource_type}}
  Body: { name: string (required), description: string, owner_id: uuid (required), metadata: object }
  Response: 201 Created with {{resource_type}} object
  Errors: 400 (validation), 409 (duplicate name), 429 (rate limited)

GET /{{resource_slug}}/{id}
  Description: Retrieve a specific {{resource_type}}
  Response: 200 OK with {{resource_type}} object, 404 if not found

PATCH /{{resource_slug}}/{id}
  Description: Update a {{resource_type}}
  Body: Partial {{resource_type}} object
  Response: 200 OK with updated object

DELETE /{{resource_slug}}/{id}
  Description: Soft-delete a {{resource_type}} (recoverable for {{number}} days)
  Response: 204 No Content

